    • Constructor Detail

      • MVIRESTClient

        public MVIRESTClient()
        Create the instance reading the connection info from "VAPI_HOST", "VAPI_PORT" (or 443 if not present) or , and "VAPI_TOKEN" environment variables.

      • MVIRESTClient

        public MVIRESTClient(String host,
                     int port,
                     String apiKey)
        Create the instance to talk to the given host over the given port using the given api key.
        Parameters:
        host - if null, look in "VAPI_HOST" and environment variables. If not provided there, the throw an IllegalArgumentException.
        port - if null and env var is not set, look in "VAPI_PORT" environment variable. If not provided there, then use 443.
        apiKey - if null, look in "VAPI_TOKEN" environment variable. If not provided there, the throw an IllegalArgumentException.

      • addFile

        public void addFile(String dsID,
                    double[][] spectrogram,
                    String labelValue)
             throws IOException
        Add the given spectrogram as an image to the given data set and attach the given label value.
        Parameters:
        dsID - id of data set to add the spectrogram image to.
        spectrogram - the spectrogram. 1st dimension is feature index (i.e. time) with each element holding a single feature for the given time. 2nd dimension is feature vector index.
        labelValue - the label to assign to the whole spectrogram
        Throws:
        IOException
